reviewText: I give this 2 stars because the ONLY play worth your time is 'What My Husband Don't Know', which is why I even bothered to buy this thing. The other 2 plays sucked like hell.
Not as good as some of Talbert's other work
Great! I watched it several times.
ALL 3 PLAYS ARE GREAT!  ALOT OF LESSONS FOR PEOPLE TO KEY IN ON, THIS COUNTRY NEEDS MORE PLAYS LIKE THIS AND LESS BULL CRAP SHOWS THAT ARE ON T.V. TODAY.
I have been a fan of David E. Talbert since the beginning so whenever he puts something out I make sure to support him. These are all three very good plays. Check them out.

Tyler perry isn't the only one who makes great plays david e talbert does too. His plays are great my favorite is what my husband doesnt know just amazing, all of them are very good!
Love David e. Talbert.  He is a genuine genius.  He has lived multiple lives and tells us the stories we want to hear
I love these movies. Should have bought them a long time ago but I like them better in a package deal

I absolutely love "What My Husband Doesn't Know". It's hilarious! I laugh so much every time the scene comes up with her best friend meeting the plumber for the first time. OMG! I didn't care much for the second dvd, "Suddenly Single", and have not watched the third.
I loved all three plays so I purchased them.
